title: Commission Regulation (EC) No 752/2009 of 17 August 2009 entering a name in the register of protected designations of origin and protected geographical indications (Batata doce de Aljezur (PGI))
header:
18.8.2009 EN Official Journal of the European Union L 213/8
COMMISSION REGULATION (EC) No 752/2009
of 17 August 2009
entering a name in the register of protected designations of origin and protected geographical indications (Batata doce de Aljezur (PGI))
THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES
recitals:
,
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community,
Having regard to Council Regulation (EC) No 510/2006 of 20 March 2006 on the protection of geographical indications and designations of origin for agricultural products and foodstuffs (1), and in particular Article 7(4) thereof,
Whereas:
(1) Pursuant to the first subparagraph of Article 6(2) of Regulation (EC) No 510/2006 and in accordance with Article 17(2) thereof, Portugal’s application to register the name ‘Batata doce de Aljezur’ was published in the Official Journal of the European Union
 (2).
(2) As no statement of objection under Article 7 of Regulation (EC) No 510/2006 has been received by the Commission, this name should be entered in the register,
main_body: The name contained in the Annex to this Regulation is hereby entered in the register.

This Regulation shall enter into force on the 20th day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Union.
This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States.
attachments:
Done at Brussels, 17 August 2009.
For the Commission
Mariann FISCHER BOEL
Member of the Commission
(1)  OJ L 93, 31.3.2006, p. 12.
(2)  OJ C 324, 19.12.2008, p. 31.
ANNEX
Agricultural products intended for human consumption listed in Annex I to the Treaty:
Class 1.6.   Fruit, vegetables and cereals, fresh or processed
PORTUGAL
Batata doce de Aljezur (PGI)
